The paper deals with accelerating Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed method involves regularization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves mathematical and empirical evaluations, which are common in data structures (cs.DS) research.
